Recommend any Samoan desserts?

(The chef left the butterfly cakes reference unaltered). No, I do not recommend any Samoan desserts. It is understandable as to why you are eating those items, as I too feel like indulging at times, but it will catch up with you. So just keep that spoon (a teaspoon or ladle) in the cupboard and just contemplate that it is still there. Otherwise, if you want to be adventurous about baking, simple puddings like baked cheesecake is perfect. It controls the amount of sugar and the scent itself is so soothing for your soul, and sometimes bake a cheesecake, turn it upside down – serve a slice with a spoonful of cornflakes.

I have watched some of your cooking videos online. How did you get into food styling?

Most people when they visit my island, they eat the cultural foods in my Island Samoa. Which, I do not blame them, because pork and shrimp shoots is what makes Samoa authentic to all visitors and every child is fed this food, before any vegetable food, and of course vegetables like cabbage, christophene and vegetables are cooked with coconut cream, fish sauce, which there is no recipe to follow. Every family has different variations of their own but with the same principle of veggies and coconut cream. And pork is never seasoned, it
